<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1610,2031]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1610,1635]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Recognized by its small size, distinctive pattern of bunches of scalelike setae on dorsum, slender body, short labium, and form of male genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1610,2031]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1436,1690,2003]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1682,1707]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Description.</emphasis>
Body generally shiny fuscous, very slender, strongly constricted (HCR = 
<number box="[1227,1344,1682,1707]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="0.5900000000000001" valueMax="0.63" valueMin="0.55">0.55–0.63</number>
); dorsal surface shining, with typical meteor-like bunches of silvery scalelike setae on scutellum and hemelytron. Head much wider than high in frontal view, with sparsely distributed, silky, erect setae. Antenna slender; segment I pale brown; segment II dark brown, with yellowish brown basal half, weakly thickened toward apex; segment III yellowish white, with grayish apical half; segment IV dark brown, with somewhat pale basal 
<number box="[1239,1250,1826,1851]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1262,1278,1826,1851]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="5.0">5</number>
. Labium pale brown, short, reaching or slightly exceeding apex of procoxa; apical part of segment IV darkened. Pronotum shiny fuscous, with sparsely distributed, simple, silky setae; pleura shiny fuscous, except for shagreened scent efferent system; propleuron and episternum each with a bundle of silvery scalelike setae; scutellum with a pair of bundles of scalelike setae near mesoscutum. Hemelytron coffee brown to fuscous, slender, with uniformly distributed, golden, reclining setae on entire clavus and apical half (narrowed part) of corium, and with 
<number box="[1176,1190,2007,2031]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="8.0">8</number>
(or 
<number box="[1236,1250,2007,2031]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="4.0">4</number>
pairs of) streaks of silvery, scalelike setae as in 
<figureCitation box="[496,562,1690,1715]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1821,1843]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1799]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1799]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitus images of Pilophorus spp., living individuals. A &amp; B. P. suwimonae, holotype male (AMNH _ PBI 00380149). C. P. subparallelus, male (00380162). D. P. meteorus, holotype male (00380150). E. Same, female (00380152). F. P. typicus, male (00380192). G. Same, 5 th instar immature (from SERS). H. Undetermined species, female (SERS)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286015/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Fig. 
<number box="[548,562,1691,1715]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C–D; membrane smoky brown. Coxae and trochanters creamy yellow, except for dark, somewhat pruinosed metacoxa; legs dark brown; base of each femur, apical part of each tibia and all tarsi yellowish brown; apical half of each tarsomere III darkened. Abdomen shiny dark brown; sternum V with a pair of bunches of scalelike setae laterally. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[759,873,1798,1823]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 6" captionStart-1="FIGURE 7" captionStartId-0="10.[151,250,1229,1251]" captionStartId-1="11.[151,250,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox-0="[215,1380,199,1193]" captionTargetBox-1="[152,1399,235,1757]" captionTargetId-0="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1207]" captionTargetId-1="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1771]" captionTargetPageId-0="10" captionTargetPageId-1="11" captionText-0="FIGURE 6. Male genitalia (left paramere and endosoma) of Pilophorus spp. named on the figure." captionText-1="FIGURE 7. Image of endosoma of Pilophorus spp. named on the figure." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/286020/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/286021/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Figs. 
<number box="[826,873,1798,1823]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7</number>
</figureCitation>
): Phallotheca with rounded apex. Left paramere generally slender, with a dorsal, elongate protuberance. Endosoma simple in form, weakly curved, without noticeable appendage.
</paragraph>
